The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 IFC keen to lend more

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, March 18: International Finance Corporation (IFC) ? the private lending arm of the World Bank ? will invest around $500 million annually over the next few years in India.

 This apart, IFC is holding discussions with banks for loans and equity investments.

 Our forecast is to invest $500 million every year in India over the coming years, said Anil Sinha, general manager of IFC. The main areas of investment will be infrastructure and manufacturing.

 IFCs current aggregate investment in India is about $1.2 billion out of which $450 million was invested last year.

 Out of the total investment, $200 million is in the form of equity in private companies. 




